Description: Fragment of a seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows two sides with each two coils of basketry, suggesting that the piece was attached between the lid and the wall of a basket. At the top an oval scarab-like seal-impression, almost complete preserved except for the central part. This central part has an oval framing line, the inside is not preserved. Outside of it a wide band with small parallel circumferential lines.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
